The paper focuses on using machine learning to assist automation engineers in decision making, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of paragraph embedding techniques and autoencoder models also suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the application of the proposed framework to Programmable Logic Controller (PLC) projects indicates a potential focus on control systems (cs.SY).
